{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5a9eee3b-7168-469a-aa0d-3482bf7203a8","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp` instead:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n\n   <!-- OR migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as usual — it routes through MTP now.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` is the v2-compatible MTP runner (keeps your existing 2.9.3 tests working with minimal changes).\n- If you're open to a larger migration, xUnit **v3** (`xunit.v3`) is the long-term path and has native MTP support.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n\nWould you like help applying these changes to a specific project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1a7398ef-2a40-4edd-a17b-4d2bfcd39d45","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":453,"requestId":"7031:39211A:DB35266:F16C2A5:69F2A7EE"},"id":"cb800da6-e439-4115-bfe7-95e60d9eb266","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:53:12.688Z","parentId":"4df49162-db60-442d-b2c7-413c3749f5db"}
